'''Idana''' is an [[unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] in [[Clay County, Kansas|Clay County]], [[Kansas]], United States. It is located near the town of [[Clay Center, Kansas|Clay Center]], south of [[US Route 24]].<ref>http://kansas.hometownlocator.com/ks/clay/idana.cfm</ref>

==History==
Idana is combination of the names of two settlers: Ida Howland and Anna Broughton.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.epodunk.com/cgi-bin/genInfo.php?locIndex=4738 | title=Profile for Idana, Kansas | publisher=[[ePodunk]] | accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>

A post office was opened in Chapmanville (an extinct town) in 1879, but it was moved to Idana in 1882 and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1980.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kshs.org/geog/geog_postoffices/search/county:CY |title=Kansas Post Offices, 1828-1961 (archived) |publisher=Kansas Historical Society |accessdate=7 June 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009130019/http://www.kshs.org/geog/geog_postoffices/search/county%3ACY |archivedate=October 9, 2013 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>

Idana was located on the [[Union Pacific Railroad]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.kgs.ku.edu/General/Geology/Clay/03_geog.html | title=Geohydrology of Clay County | publisher=Kansas Geological Survey | accessdate=2 August 2014}}</ref>

